==English==

===Etymology===
From ''micro-'' (small, tiny) + ''-fauna'' (animals).

===Noun===
'''microfauna''' (''plural'' '''microfaunae''' or '''microfaunas''')

# The smallest of the [[faunal]] size divisions, including mainly [[microorganism]]s but also sometimes applied to the tiniest [[species]] of [[animal]] groups such as [[tick]]s, [[insect]]s, etc.

